   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, William R. Story in Greeneville, Tenn. to John J. King, 1865 August 16</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated August 16, 1865, to John J. King, William R. Story discusses the opening of a post of the Freedmen's Bureau in Greeneville, Tennessee. Additionally, he notes the rumor of a Freedmen's court opening in Bristol to deal with a number of reported cases of abuse. Story encourages King to abandon "old political ideas" in order to avoid increased suffering.</abstract>
